title: SEC Settles Charges of Non-Compliant Trading with Latour
text:
High-frequency trading firm Latour Trading LLC agreed to pay more than $8 million to settle charges from the Securities and Exchange Commission that it violated trading norms with improper computer coding, among other errors.
